---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title={`Work — ${SITE_TITLE}`}
      description="Writing, production, and strategy work from Mazze LeCzzare Frazer — B2B content, podcast hosting, and community practice."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>

      <!-- Page header -->
      <div class="work-header">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">Work</p>
        <h1 class="page-title">Portfolio</h1>
        <p class="page-desc">Writing, production, and content strategy across B2B SaaS, game development, and community practice.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- 01 — Writing -->
      <section class="work-section" aria-labelledby="writing-label">
        <p class="section-label" id="writing-label"><span>01 — Writing</span></p>

        <div class="work-grid">

          <!-- Spec piece: Bandwidth -->
          <article class="work-card">
            <div class="card-top">
              <div class="card-tags">
                <span class="tag tag--teal">Thought Leadership</span>
                <span class="tag tag--teal">B2B</span>
                <span class="tag tag--coral">Spec Sample</span>
              </div>
              <span class="card-venue">Written for Bandwidth</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="card-title">Why Most AI Voice Deployments Stall at Scale — And What the Ones That Don't Have in Common</h2>
            <p class="card-desc">
              A spec blog post written for Bandwidth's audience of enterprise IT buyers and communications leaders. Translates infrastructure complexity into strategic framing — using Bandwidth's real product positioning (Maestro, Communications Cloud, Bring Your Own AI) without reading like a brochure.
            </p>
            <button class="expand-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="sample-bandwidth">
              Read the piece
              <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4"/></svg>
            </button>

            <div class="sample-body" id="sample-bandwidth" role="region" aria-label="Full article text" hidden>
              <p class="sample-note">✦ Written as a portfolio sample — not published</p>

              <h2>Why Most AI Voice Deployments Stall at Scale — And What the Ones That Don't Have in Common</h2>

              <p>There's a gap between an impressive AI voice demo and a production deployment your customers actually trust.</p>
              <p>Most enterprises have crossed the first threshold. The demo works. The conversational AI handles the test scenarios cleanly. Stakeholders are convinced. Then the rollout begins — and somewhere between pilot and production, the experience degrades. Latency spikes. Audio quality drops. The AI mishears. Customers abandon the interaction and call a human anyway.</p>
              <p>The problem usually isn't the AI model. It's the infrastructure underneath it.</p>
              <hr />

              <h3>The Layer Nobody Audits in the Demo</h3>
              <p>When you evaluate a conversational AI platform, you're evaluating the model's language understanding, its integration capabilities, its interface. What rarely gets stress-tested is the voice transport layer — the network path a call actually travels before it reaches your AI, and back out again before the customer hears a response.</p>
              <p>In a demo environment, that path is short and controlled. In production, you're routing calls across carrier networks, through cloud infrastructure, across geographies, with real-world variability in latency, packet loss, and jitter. The AI model that sounded natural in testing can sound robotic or stilted when the audio quality feeding it isn't clean.</p>
              <p>This is why network ownership matters in a way that's easy to underestimate. When your CPaaS provider also owns the network, they can optimize the full path — not just hand the call off at the edge and hope for the best.</p>
              <hr />

              <h3>"Bring Your Own AI" Requires Bringing the Right Foundation</h3>
              <p>Enterprise IT teams are increasingly sophisticated about AI model selection. They've evaluated OpenAI, Google, Cognigy, and a dozen vertical-specific platforms. They have preferences. They've built internal tooling around specific APIs.</p>
              <p>The smart infrastructure strategy isn't to force a single AI provider — it's to build a foundation flexible enough to support whichever model performs best for a given use case, and resilient enough to swap as the landscape evolves.</p>
              <p>That flexibility only works if the underlying communications infrastructure is genuinely model-agnostic and built to handle production-grade voice quality at scale. Otherwise, you've made your AI strategy portable but left your infrastructure brittle.</p>
              <p>The enterprises getting this right in 2026 are thinking about voice infrastructure the same way they think about cloud compute: as a strategic capability, not a commodity line item.</p>
              <hr />

              <h3>What "Production-Ready" Actually Looks Like</h3>
              <p>The deployments that hold up share a few characteristics:</p>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>They treat latency as a product requirement, not an ops problem.</strong> Every 100ms of added latency in a voice interaction changes the conversational feel. Teams that address this early in architecture decisions end up with meaningfully better customer experiences.</li>
                <li><strong>They build for fallback.</strong> AI voice agents will encounter edge cases the model hasn't seen. Production deployments have graceful handoff paths to human agents, and they instrument those handoffs to feed back into model improvement.</li>
                <li><strong>They separate the AI layer from the transport layer.</strong> When the model and the network are too tightly coupled, updating one becomes a deployment event for both. Decoupling them gives teams the ability to iterate on AI capabilities without touching call routing — and vice versa.</li>
              </ul>
              <p>The enterprises that moved from AI experimentation to deployment at scale didn't get there by finding a better model. They got there by building a foundation that let their models perform the way they did in the lab.</p>
              <p>That foundation is an infrastructure decision. Make it early.</p>
              <hr />
              <p><em>Bandwidth's Communications Cloud and Maestro orchestration platform give enterprise teams the network-native foundation and model flexibility to deploy AI voice in production — across 65+ countries and the full stack of leading UCaaS and CCaaS platforms.</em></p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <!-- LinkedIn article -->
          <article class="work-card">
            <div class="card-top">
              <div class="card-tags">
                <span class="tag tag--teal">Editorial</span>
                <span class="tag tag--teal">B2B</span>
              </div>
              <span class="card-venue">LinkedIn · 2023</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="card-title">Tips for Indie Game Developers: Approaching Publishers with Confidence and Style</h2>
            <p class="card-desc">Published under the mudstack brand to a B2B audience of game developers, studio founders, and producers. Translates high-stakes business strategy — publisher relationships, deal negotiation, portfolio positioning — into actionable guidance without losing the voice of the community it was written for.</p>
            <a class="card-link" href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/tips-indie-game-developers-approaching-publishers-confidence-" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="Read article on LinkedIn (opens in new tab)">
              Read on LinkedIn
              <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4"/></svg>
            </a>
          </article>

          <!-- We All Float On -->
          <article class="work-card">
            <div class="card-top">
              <div class="card-tags">
                <span class="tag tag--teal">Personal Essay</span>
                <span class="tag tag--teal">Science &amp; Technology</span>
              </div>
              <span class="card-venue">mazzeleczzare.com · March 2026</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="card-title">We All Float On</h2>
            <p class="card-desc">An essay on cognition, inference, and the relationship between human judgment and artificial intelligence — framed through the history of scientific discovery. Moves from Kepler and Dirac to language models and the question of what it means to navigate uncertainty with purpose.</p>
            <a class="card-link" href="/blog/we-all-float-on/" aria-label="Read We All Float On">
              Read the essay
              <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4"/></svg>
            </a>
          </article>

          <!-- 80.lv feature -->
          <article class="work-card">
            <div class="card-top">
              <div class="card-tags">
                <span class="tag tag--teal">Feature Interview</span>
                <span class="tag tag--teal">B2B SaaS</span>
              </div>
              <span class="card-venue">80.lv · September 2023</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="card-title">Unveiling the VR Vision Team's Journey: Crafting Virtual Worlds and Future Innovations</h2>
            <p class="card-desc">A cross-published feature written for mudstack on 80.lv — one of the largest editorial platforms in game development. Profiled VR Vision's enterprise XR work and their integration of mudstack into a complex multi-team art pipeline. Translated technical production workflow into narrative for a 400K+ developer and artist audience.</p>
            <a class="card-link" href="https://80.lv/articles/unveiling-the-vr-vision-team-s-journey-crafting-virtual-worlds-and-future-innovations" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="Read the VR Vision feature on 80.lv (opens in new tab)">
              Read on 80.lv
              <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4"/></svg>
            </a>
          </article>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 02 — Production -->
      <section class="work-section" aria-labelledby="production-label">
        <p class="section-label" id="production-label"><span>02 — Production</span></p>

        <div class="prod-grid">

          <!-- Podcast -->
          <article class="prod-card">
            <svg class="prod-icon" viewBox="0 0 36 36" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" aria-hidden="true">
              <circle cx="18" cy="13" r="5"/>
              <path d="M10 20c0 4.4 3.6 8 8 8s8-3.6 8-8"/>
              <line x1="18" y1="28" x2="18" y2="33"/>
              <line x1="13" y1="33" x2="23" y2="33"/>
            </svg>
            <h2 class="prod-title">Clear as Mud</h2>
            <p class="prod-desc">Host and producer of 50+ interview episodes featuring creators and executives from Epic Games, Riot Games, Sony PlayStation, and Meta VR. Full lifecycle ownership: topic ideation, speaker outreach, scripting, production, and multi-format distribution.</p>
            <a class="card-link" href="https://open.spotify.com/show/50eMqYFskikUzz4EuoYTyf" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="Listen to Clear as Mud on Spotify (opens in new tab)">
              Listen on Spotify
              <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4"/></svg>
            </a>
          </article>

          <!-- Webinar: Publisher pitching -->
          <article class="prod-card">
            <svg class="prod-icon" viewBox="0 0 36 36" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" aria-hidden="true">
              <rect x="3" y="6" width="30" height="20" rx="2"/>
              <line x1="13" y1="30" x2="23" y2="30"/>
              <line x1="18" y1="26" x2="18" y2="30"/>
              <polygon points="14,13 14,21 24,17" fill="currentColor" stroke="none"/>
            </svg>
            <h2 class="prod-title">How To Pitch Your Game to a Publisher &amp; Why You Should</h2>
            <p class="prod-desc">Produced and hosted for mudstack, featuring Bobby Wertheim (VP of Partnerships, Curve Games) and Lauren Hunter. Managed full production lifecycle — topic framing, speaker outreach, run-of-show, live production, and post-event distribution.</p>
            <a class="card-link" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rdsgB1Uoi-Q" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="Watch webinar on YouTube (opens in new tab)">
              Watch on YouTube
              <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4"/></svg>
            </a>
          </article>

          <!-- Webinar: Breaking into game dev -->
          <article class="prod-card">
            <svg class="prod-icon" viewBox="0 0 36 36" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" aria-hidden="true">
              <rect x="3" y="6" width="30" height="20" rx="2"/>
              <line x1="13" y1="30" x2="23" y2="30"/>
              <line x1="18" y1="26" x2="18" y2="30"/>
              <polygon points="14,13 14,21 24,17" fill="currentColor" stroke="none"/>
            </svg>
            <h2 class="prod-title">Breaking Into Game Dev as a Digital Artist</h2>
            <p class="prod-desc">Produced and hosted for mudstack, featuring Matt Wright (Environment Art Director, Bad Robot Games) and Jonathan Lloyd (Founder &amp; CEO, CG Hero). Covered portfolio strategy, studio hiring expectations, networking, and common application mistakes.</p>
            <a class="card-link" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gSPVU7Omat0" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="Watch webinar on YouTube (opens in new tab)">
              Watch on YouTube
              <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4"/></svg>
            </a>
          </article>

          <!-- Webinar: Virtual production -->
          <article class="prod-card">
            <svg class="prod-icon" viewBox="0 0 36 36" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" aria-hidden="true">
              <rect x="3" y="6" width="30" height="20" rx="2"/>
              <line x1="13" y1="30" x2="23" y2="30"/>
              <line x1="18" y1="26" x2="18" y2="30"/>
              <polygon points="14,13 14,21 24,17" fill="currentColor" stroke="none"/>
            </svg>
            <h2 class="prod-title">Exploring the Future of Virtual Production</h2>
            <p class="prod-desc">Produced and hosted for mudstack, featuring HaZ Dulull — film director and virtual production pioneer. Discussed how real-time technology and LED volumes are reshaping the pipeline for indie creators and studio productions alike.</p>
            <a class="card-link" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eLk2LYeYa0Q" target="_blank" rel="noopener" aria-label="Watch virtual production webinar on YouTube (opens in new tab)">
              Watch on YouTube
              <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4"/></svg>
            </a>
          </article>

        </div>
      </section>

    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  main {
    max-width: 900px;
    width: calc(100% - 2rem);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1rem 6rem;
  }

  /* ── Page header ── */
  .work-header {
    padding: 4em 0 3em;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .section-eyebrow {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68em;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-faint);
    margin-bottom: 0.75em;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0 0 0.5em;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }

  .page-desc {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82em;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 56ch;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* ── Section wrapper ── */
  .work-section {
    padding: 3.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .work-section:last-of-type {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.8rem;
  }
  .section-label::after {
    content: '';
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--rule);
  }

  /* ── Work cards ── */
  .work-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .work-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 2rem 2.2rem;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: border-color var(--transition-base), box-shadow var(--transition-base);
  }
  .work-card::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(58, 184, 160, 0.04);
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity var(--transition-base);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .work-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(58, 184, 160, 0.3);
    box-shadow: 0 0 28px rgba(58, 184, 160, 0.12);
  }
  .work-card:hover::before { opacity: 1; }

  .card-top {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .card-tags { display: flex; gap: 0.4em; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  .tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.2em 0.65em;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    color: var(--text-faint);
  }
  .tag--teal { border-color: var(--teal); color: var(--teal); }
  .tag--coral { border-color: var(--coral); color: var(--coral); }

  .card-venue {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--text-faint);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .card-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.2vw, 1.45rem);
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .card-desc {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  .card-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.45rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: gap var(--transition-fast);
  }
  .card-link:hover { gap: 0.75rem; }
  .card-link svg { width: 14px; height: 14px; flex-shrink: 0; }

  /* ── Expand/collapse spec piece ── */
  .expand-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.45rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--teal);
    background: none;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 0;
    transition: gap var(--transition-fast);
  }
  .expand-btn:hover { gap: 0.75rem; }
  .expand-btn svg { width: 14px; height: 14px; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .expand-btn:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--teal); outline-offset: 3px; border-radius: 2px; }

  .sample-body {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .sample-body[hidden] { display: none; }

  .sample-body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 2.5vw, 1.8rem);
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .sample-body h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--teal);
    margin: 2rem 0 0.5rem;
  }
  .sample-body p {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
  }
  .sample-body strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }
  .sample-body hr {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    margin: 1.75rem 0;
  }
  .sample-body ul {
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .sample-body li {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .sample-note {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    background: rgba(232, 112, 90, 0.06);
    border: 1px solid rgba(232, 112, 90, 0.25);
    color: var(--coral);
    padding: 0.35em 0.9em;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  /* ── Production grid ── */
  .prod-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prod-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 1.6rem 1.8rem;
    transition: border-color var(--transition-base), box-shadow var(--transition-base);
  }
  .prod-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(58, 184, 160, 0.3);
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(58, 184, 160, 0.1);
  }

  .prod-icon {
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--teal);
  }

  .prod-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .prod-desc {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .prod-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .card-top { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
    .work-card { padding: 1.5rem; }
    .prod-card { padding: 1.25rem; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const btn = document.querySelector<HTMLButtonElement>('.expand-btn');
  const body = document.getElementById('sample-bandwidth');

  if (btn && body) {
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const isOpen = !body.hidden;
      body.hidden = isOpen;
      btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(!isOpen));
      const textNode = btn.childNodes[0];
      if (textNode && textNode.nodeType === Node.TEXT_NODE) {
        textNode.textContent = isOpen ? 'Read the piece ' : 'Close ';
      }
      if (!isOpen) {
        body.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'nearest' });
      }
    });
  }
</script>
